  "prompt": "Can I claim HRA during ITR Filing?",
  "response": "Yes, you can claim House Rent Allowance (HRA) during Income Tax Return (ITR) filing if you meet certain conditions:\n\nEligibility Criteria:\n1. You receive HRA as part of your salary\n2. You are actually paying rent for accommodation\n3. You are living in a rented house/apartment\n\nDocumentation Required:\n1. Rent receipts\n2. Rental agreement\n3. PAN of landlord (if annual rent exceeds \u20b91 lakh)\n\nCalculation Method:\nHRA exemption is the least of:\n- Actual HRA received from employer\n- 50% of basic salary (metro cities)\n- 40% of basic salary (non-metro cities)\n- Actual rent paid minus 10% of basic salary\n\nAdditional Conditions:\n- Must have proof of rent payment\n- Should not own a house in the same city\n- Rent paid to family members is not eligible\n- Rental agreement should be genuine\n\nSteps to Claim:\n1. Collect rent receipts\n2. Fill appropriate section in ITR form\n3. Provide supporting documents\n4. Submit declaration during filing\n\nConsult a tax professional for personalized advice about your specific situation.",
